article.headline: Youngblood scores 23 in South Florida's 89-73 victory over Albany

images.name: Kasean Pryor throws down big slam dunk vs. Albany Great Danes
images.caption: Kasean Pryor throws down big slam dunk vs. Albany Great Danes

article.linkText: Youngblood scores 23 in South Florida's 89-73 victory over Albany
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. -- — Chris Youngblood had 23 points in South Florida's 89-73 win over Albany on Friday. Youngblood shot 8 for 13 (1 for 4 from 3-point range) and 6 of 8 from the free throw line for the Bulls (6-4). Kasean Pryor added 21 points while going 8 of 15 from the floor, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and 4 for 8 from the line, and he also had eight rebounds. Sam Hines Jr. finished 6 of 8 from the field to finish with 13 points. Amar'e Marshall led the Great Danes (7-6) in scoring, finishing with 19 points, eight rebounds and three steals. Jonathan Beagle added 17 points and nine rebounds for Albany. In addition, Sebastian Thomas finished with 17 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
